summary: can you write a fic where Reed gets high and thinks TJ is a branch
question: can you write a fic where Reed gets high and thinks TJ is a branch
answer:
😍😍iconic

TJ looked down at his phone. He was late. Twenty minutes late. He sighed and looked down the street, did he even want to go at this point? Reed and Lester would be at least two bowls in, TJ wouldn’t be able to catch up, and he really didn’t want to. He could at least hang out, he reasoned, watching Reed blazed was always entertaining. Perhaps he could convince him to go out, ride bikes or fuck around town. Yeah, he’d go.

Reed’s house was only five minutes down the street, but that was another five minutes for the boys already there to get higher. TJ heard them talking—laughing—as he approached Reed’s Shack. He tried to listen to gage where they were.

“No, no, no, man,” he heard Reed say. “It’s like, the opposite, look. Look at him, Kippen is totally GONE.” TJ frowned, what? “He’s on like a-another field of existence right now,” Reed continued. “Look.” He heard a thrash of sound, followed by, “See? Gone.” TJ assumed they were still talking about him, yet he had no idea what they were saying. He pulled open the wooden door and walked in.

“How high are we, boys?” TJ announced. Reed looked at him and jumped, tipping over backwards off the speaker he was using as a chair. TJ chuckled and then looked to Lester, raising an eyebrow.

Reed scrambled back up, looking to TJ and then across the room, then back at TJ. “Wh—? TJ?” He asked, his eyes wide, and bloodshot. TJ laughed harder, kid looked out of it.

“That’s me,” TJ confirmed.

“If you’re there, then who have we been talking to?” Reed questioned, his head spinning. TJ was about to ask what the hell that meant, when Reed pointed across the room. “Who is that?” He asked. TJ followed his finger. He was pointing at one of the tree branches that protruded through his shack.

TJ blinked, were they really that dumb? “And you are referring to?”

“The dude,” Reed said, emphasising where he was pointing, “Right there.”

TJ looked to Lester, who nodded, agreeing with Reed. “You dumb fucks that’s a tree,” he said.

Reed frowned, squinting at it, “What?”

TJ walked up and slapped his hand against it. “See? Always been here, always been a tree.”

Reed cautiously walked up behind him, mimicking his slap, but much lighter. “Oh shit!” He laughed. “That’s my tree!”

TJ rolled his eyes and then dropped down onto the futon against the wall. “So what are we at? Four bowls?”

Reed shook his head with a goofy smile, “I dunno, man, I haven’t been sober today.”

TJ nodded, that sounded accurate.

summary: "Be a friend, Be a hero, Be safe together" had some very interesting choices around word placements in that psa. Probably best...
question: "Be a friend, Be a hero, Be safe together" had some very interesting choices around word placements in that psa. Probably best not to read into it as the gun story is its own thing but I'm genuinely starting to believe Terri did get permission from Disney for cannon Tyrus. Looking back on Josh's comments, his clues don't seem as bad. All that's happened is a change in how Tyrus get together for him, not that they don't get together at all. The carnival episode is going to be big I feel it
answer: Yup. Idk if we can gage from the gun story line too much but the main thing is: Cyrus can’t just let TJ go, his feelings are overpowering everything and everyone that is telling him TJ is a bad influence, he can’t believe it. I feel like his feelings have to come forward from this, it’s the only real explanation he has, and either he’s realising his feelings are why he’s so reluctant to drop TJ or he knows and he’s going to tell his friends.
